Activity overview
In this lab activity, youâ€™ll use the Advanced Package Tool (APT) and sudo to install and uninstall applications in a Linux Bash shell.

--
Debian basedLinux using Bash CLI

Task 1: Ensure that APT is installed
  [apt is Debian based package manager]

~$ apt


Task 2. Install and uninstall the Suricata application
  [network analysis tool used for intrusion detection]

~$ sudo apt install suricata
~ sudo apt remove suricata -y

> Check to see if installed and removed by trying to run the application 
  ~$ suricata

Task 3. Install the tcpdump application
  [Use the APT package manager to list all installed applications.]

~$ sudo apt tcpdump

Task 4. List the installed applications

~$ apt list --installed
Task 5. Reinstall the Suricata application
